Dataset

The experiments in this project were conducted using the "COCO128" dataset, which is a small subset of the Microsoft COCO dataset commonly used for object detection research.

COCO128 contains labeled images with bounding box annotations for multiple object categories including vehicles such as cars, trucks, and buses.

This dataset is widely used for quick experimentation and benchmarking of object detection models.

Dataset Source:
https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov5/releases/download/v1.0/coco128.zip

For larger-scale evaluation, the models can also be tested on aerial object detection datasets such as "VisDrone" and "UAVDT", which are commonly used in drone-based surveillance research.
